                                    <p>Multiple marble fragments (of which three join to make one larger fragment, and a
                                        fourth is approximately contiguous to the main fragment), which appear to form
                                        part of the circular basin of a 'louterion'. The remains of a square projection
                                        (12 x 12 cm, projecting a further 6 cm from the base) are partly preserved on
                                        the reverse of the main fragment, by which the basin was fixed onto the stand.
                                    </p>
